description.3: The X-Men come upon a massacred Shi'Ar transport headed for the heart of the empire. The only survivor needs their help.
description.5: Shang-Chi teams with the X-Men to investigate Sebastian Shaw and his research into a cure for the Legacy Virus. Will Shaw and the Hellfire Club use a possible cure to save mutantkind or use it to make an enormous profit?
description.9: ENTER THE DRAGONFLY! A group of ninjas called "The True Believers", led by Karsano follow through on a ritual that allows them 3 attempts to kill Angela Yin. Failing to do so, Karsano commits ritual suicide. Unfortunately, this is not the end of the Dragonfly.
description.16: Spider-Man, Ka-zar, and Shanna get some help from Stegron the Dinosaur Man!
description.21: Everything you need to know about the far-out Bug from outer space is right here in this issue!
description.23: When Doc Ock and Venom team up, Spider-Man must swing into action before MJ pays the price! Concluding the series based on the hit animated show!
description.26: This man making a bid for the throne of the Royal Citadel of Eiattu-this man who would lead the People's Liberation Battalion to rule this world-claims to be the brother of the current ruler, Princess Plourr. But Plourr knows-with great certainty-that this cannot be. To reveal the truth might destroy his power, but it could, in turn, destroy her as well.
description.27: Gav and Jori Daragon knew they could be killed in their chosen line of work - mapping out uncharted hyperspace flight paths could easily result in a deadly meeting with an unexpected meteorite shower or an unknown world. But it's neither comets nor planets that threaten them now. Rather, it's their success that may cost them their lives. They've successfully mapped a hyperspace shortcut - a shortcut which could prove strategically imperative in the event of war. And war is just what Gav and Jori have found themselves in the middle of. Trapped between two factions of the Sith, each vying for control of the galaxy, this sibling duo of hyperspace pioneers has become a pawn to the dark side.
description.33: Like the Special Edition of the motion picture, this comics series will take you back to a place you've never been before! Experience it again, for the very first time.
description.34: Before the Battle of Yavin, the Rogue Squadron gets in a dogfight with TIE fighters. Plus, who is the new member of Rogue Squadron?
description.35: Logan and Carol Danvers…facing off against Sabretooth and the Hellfire Club!
description.36: The mysterious mystical entity known as The Architect opens a competition for hired mercenaries and assassins.
description.39: Is the Hulk seeing double? It's business as usual for Hulk, locking horns with his nemesis Wildman, but things take a turn for the weird when the Incredible Hulk comes face to face with...the Incredible Hulk!?
description.43: Cannonball versus Gladiator! Plus, Joseph has a special gift for Rogue.
description.48: Eddie Brock… reunited with the Venom symbiote! And Doctor Octopus is to blame!
description.51: The Future Imperfect refugees try to kill the Abomination of the present to save their future. But does that mean the newborn child of the Maestro is in danger as well?
description.54: The Badoon have captured the Star-Lord! Sharing a jail cell with a Spartax criminal and a Badoon child aren't exactly Peter's idea of a good time...Luckily, Peter's got an ace up his sleeve - an ace named Kitty Pryde!
description.55: With El-Uno still alive, Spidey takes a break to search for Mary-Jane's Christmas present. On his journey, he meets X-MAN who accompanies him on an assignment. The gift giving continues when Black Tarantula receives a Christmas gift: El Uno's head on a wreath.
description.63: In the aftermath of Onslaught, a de-powered Professor X is imprisoned in an abandoned Hulkbuster base without hope of freedom. Will Charles Xavier find an ally in prisoner M-9, a young girl with incredible mutant abilities?
description.65: Spider-Man teams up with Ka-zar and Shanna the She-Devil to save the Savage Land from a complete disaster caused by Roxxon scientists.
description.70: Crown, crown-who's got the crown? Plourr Ilo has reluctantly taken it on, but finds being a princess can be even rougher than being a warrior. Her brother instead wants to destroy the crown, not knowing that his own lover intends to claim-not only the crown, but the planet-for herself! And as the different factions battle it out, the Empire waits in the wings, waiting to claim whatever remains. But standing in their way is the fabled Rogue Squadron-and they've decided to take out the Empire, one TIE fighter at a time!
description.71: Boba Fett'is the most feared, most respected'bounty hunter'in'the galaxy. He only cares about two things: his money and his reputation. So when he discovers someone has been impersonating him, he decides to teach his inferior doppleg'nger'exactly why he's the most feared, most respected bounty hunter in the galaxy! It's Boba Fett vs. Boba Fett!
description.75: When Gav and Jori Daragon were first captured by the evil Sith, they feared for their lives. Now, Jori fears for her brother's spirit, as would-be Dark Lord Naga Sadow begins to initiate him into the ways of the dark side of the Force. Naga Sadow is playing a deadly game of chess, and the Daragon siblings are his pawns.
description.76: Experience the Star Wars Universe as you experience it on the big screen, with this special edition mini-series! Re-discover your favorite characters and moments with this exclusive collection of stories!
description.78: Spider-Man's Clone Saga has spun completely out of control! There's only one team that can save the wall-crawler now: the Marvel editors! Bob Harras, Ralph Macchio, Tom Brevoort, and more put their heads together to see if ANYTHING can get Spidey out of this doppelganger debacle!
description.80: Elektra deals with the guilt over letting Nina's parents die. Nina gets caught up with some criminals with ulterior motives, but Elektra intervenes just in time. Meanwhile the Architect continues unfolding his plan.
description.85: THE BITE OF THE BLACK TARANTULA IS ALWAYS... FATAL! Spider-man vs. The Black Tarantula! Spidey must stop the Black Tarantula from expanding his influence in the city with an illegal emerald trade.
description.89: Peter's captured by a bounty hunter - who may have a strange connection to his past! Can Peter and the bounty hunter make amends before he's fed to a giant alien? And who is the mysterious Mr. Knife--and why is he so interested in Star-Lord?
description.92: The Trapster is back and ready for his shining moment!

2.text: Doctor Doom has captured Ben, Sue, and Black Panther! Can Ben and Johnny rescue their teammates? And just who is Wyatt Wingfoot?

5.text: Shang-Chi teams with the X-Men to investigate Sebastian Shaw and his research into a cure for the Legacy Virus. Will Shaw and the Hellfire Club use a possible cure to save mutantkind or use it to make an enormous profit?

7.text: It’s an OG Defenders reunion when Doctor Strange shows up! The Sorcerer Supreme enters the Surfer’s psyche to unblock an emotional barrier stemming from Norrin Radd. But what is Galactus doing in the farthest corners of Norrin’s mind?

11.text: Whirlwind has taken Pepper Potts hostage! Plus, Bruce Banner reveals the truth to Leonard Samson.

13.text: Franklin Richards…a mutant? Reed and Sue Richard’s eldest son may have powers beyond the X-Men’s understanding.

14.text: Following last issue's confrontation, Madelyne must answer for her crimes against Threnody. Nate and Jean Grey demand vengeance!

17.text: WHO IS THE REAL HOBGOBLIN? Facing death, Spider-Man must find out who the real Hobgoblin is before it’s too late.

18.text: Domino will need her luckiest break yet in order to free herself from Donald Pierce and Lady Deathstrike! Not to mention, her old flame is still in need of rescue!

19.text: When Venom is incarcerated, Matt Murdock steps up to be his attorney pro bono!

20.text: Double-sized anniversary issue! The secret conspirator of Mondo is revealed! What ties do they have to Banshee? And what nefarious plans do they have for the students of Generation X?

24.text: With the Shi’ar Empire, the Watcher, the Living Tribunal and more universal forces drawn into the fray, brace yourself for a big finish on a cosmic scale!

25.text: The Lethal Protector’s origin! Eddie Brock was a disgraced journalist looking for an extra boost in his otherwise ordinary life. Never could he anticipate this ‘boost’ would come in the form of Venom, an alien symbiote that bonded to Eddie and became one of Spider-Man’s fiercest foes!

30.text: Rikki Barnes suits up to save her brother from the brainwashing indoctrination of the World Party. Meanwhile, Cap and Sam Wilson are prisoners of the Red Skull!

31.text: Deadpool's buddy, Weasel, has been kidnapped by the nefarious Taskmaster! But is this a grand trap for our hero or a super-villanous job offer? Only the army of ninjas knows for sure.

32.text: The lethal Headsman has an arms supplier who is all too familiar to Spider-Man.

35.text: Logan and Carol Danvers…facing off against Sabretooth and the Hellfire Club!

36.text: The mysterious mystical entity known as The Architect opens a competition for hired mercenaries and assassins.

37.text: Molten Man looks for help while Daredevil reunites with Black Widow!

38.text: Colossus faces his inner demons and Magneto’s Acolytes!

42.text: During a scientific mission in Wakanda, an entire group of scientists is wiped out by an unknown force. The Fantastic Four set out to investigate.

45.text: Cyclops arrives with the cavalry to save Storm from Candra’s “magic show”. Who will possess the soul gem by the end of this issue?

47.text: Silver Surfer attempts to recover memories from his old friend and fellow Defender, the Hulk. But the jade giant is on a not-so-jolly rampage and Surfer needs to figure out why!

49.text: Things take a turn toward darkness and despair as the team steps into the shadow of…the Man-Thing!

50.text: Braniac Beast gets his own Uncanny Origin! Read up on the High school football star-turned science whiz who forged his own destiny as one of the Original Five X-Men!

51.text: The Future Imperfect refugees try to kill the Abomination of the present to save their future. But does that mean the newborn child of the Maestro is in danger as well?

52.text: Despite being seriously injured, Gambit must find Anielle before it’s too late!

54.text: With the corrupt forces of Lawgiver Damyish set at their throats, Quarrel must continue his masquerade as Starlord, but does he have what it takes to get the job done?

57.text: Iron Man versus The Living Laser! How far will a man with a fiber optic nervous system go to enact revenge on Tony Stark?

59.text: Enter...Morbius the Living Vampire! X-Man falls victim to Morbius' bite and turns to Spidey for help!

62.text: Christmas time is here again! On the eve of the holiday, the Gen X'ers gather around and share untold stories of their past involving the early days of their mutant powers manifesting.

66.text: UNCOVERING THE TRUTH! The Hobgoblin is back and on the loose! Can Spider-Man stop him before another death is added to the tally?

67.text: The Daily Bugle has seen it all…until the day Betty Brant was taken hostage!

68.text: Donald Pierce is all that stands between Domino and her kidnapped flame…well, Donald Pierce AND Lady Deathstrike!

69.text: Venom and Wolverine must put aside their differences to stop Chimera from releasing Cyber Wraiths on the universe.

72.text: What happened to Captain America after World War II? Nick Fury divulges this top secret information! Plus, Cap is attacked by Crossbones at the funeral of Abraham Wilson!

73.text: Why is Spider-Man on the wrong side of Hawkeye’s arrow? Black Widow makes an appearance.

77.text: After being rejected by Nephri, En Sabah Nur goes on a furious rampage! What will happen when he gains Rama-Tut's secret to ruling his kingdom. Ancient Egypt, prepare for the APOCALYPSE!

78.text: Spider-Man's Clone Saga has spun completely out of control! There's only one team that can save the wall-crawler now: the Marvel editors! Bob Harras, Ralph Macchio, Tom Brevoort, and more put their heads together to see if ANYTHING can get Spidey out of this doppelganger debacle!

79.text: A new cop discovers what it is to work the super hero beat. Marvel takes to the streets in this gritty, and groundbreaking, series!

80.text: Elektra deals with the guilt over letting Nina's parents die. Nina gets caught up with some criminals with ulterior motives, but Elektra intervenes just in time. Meanwhile the Architect continues unfolding his plan.

81.text: Tony Stark and Bruce Banner have gone missing! The government calls in The Fantastic Four to investigate.

83.text: Nate comes to an ‘understanding' with Bishop. Maddie cements her new role amongst the Hellfire Club's Inner Circle.

86.text: After being emotionally overridden by Pyscho-Man, both Cable and Kane seek revenge in an ‘Innerspace Rebellion’!

87.text: A shooting star has fallen to Earth in the form of a woman, and it’s up to Gambit to protect the celestial body from those who wish to abuse her power.

89.text: As Sinjin Quarrel and Aurora follow the trail of the original Starlord, they make a startling discovery!

90.text: Featuring love stories from your favorite Marvel couples! Guest-starring the Goddess of Love, Venus!

91.text: Cordelia Frost wants to join the Hellfire Club as White Queen, no matter what the cost is! And what secrets has M been hiding from the team?

93.text: WILL THE REAL HOBGOBLIN PLEASE STAND UP! Jason Macendale’s arrest for Hobgoblin activities brings up many theories and questions on who the REAL Hobgoblin is…

94.text: J. Jonah Jameson is on the prowl for a story, and we all know what that means! Troubles a comin'.

95.text: Master scribe Brian K. Vaughan pits Ka-Zar against three enemies, one of whom is a cosmic entity!

96.text: Domino finds out that an old lover has been kidnapped from a federal complex. She immediately begins planning a daring rescue!

97.text: With Dirt Nap after Venom and Wolverine, the two antiheroes must team up to escape a bizarre dimension!

98.text: Humans are being caged while the Gene Nationals call for genocide!

99.text: Uncomfortable feelings are set aside when Joseph, Rogue and Gambit confront a foe who will stop at nothing to end them!
